imdb.plot outline: The story of Joaquin Bordado begins when the assassin gets a new mission to kill the head of an illegal arms dealer group. Joaquin vows that this will be his last mission. He wants to leave behind his dark secret of being an assassin of a special military service and live a peaceful life with his family and be a loving husband to his wife who is unaware of his secret identity. Unknown to Joaquin, the truth is bound to unveil and his last mission will lead him to a series of unfortunate events. Joaquin is set to fulfill his mission when he discovers a secret that totally changed his life and all his plans. Then he finds himself behind bars. Yet despite what happened, he continues to hope that someday he will live a happy and peaceful life with his family. Inside the jail, Joaquin will meet Jilco, an old mysterious man whose body is filled with tattoos. But while he meets new comrades in prison, he also meets new enemies to fight -- one of whom would be the cause of his death. But Joaquin won't die for long. Jilco, who comes from the land of the witches, will resurrect Joaquin -- the chosen heir who will continue the mission to defend the good from all evil with the help of powerful tattoos -- Miguela (cherubim), Aratu (rat), Asaru (snake), Kris (sword), Lamina (eagle), Jihasu (jaguar), Orago (dragon), and warrior girl Erenea. With his new power, Joaquin faces a new life with a new mission. How will he be able to deal with his powers? And how long will Joaquin stand this new mission when his family is slowly drifting away from him? Will Joaquin be able to find his way back to the arms of his beloved wife or will his new mission lead him to a new love?
imdb.title: Joaquin Bordado
plot: _Joaquin Bordado_ (qv) is a man with tattoos all over his body. What is unique about these tattoos are they become alive.::iGMA.tv
